A tragic train collision in Los Angeles was caused by a suicidal man, Juan Manuel Alvarez, who parked his Jeep on the tracks.
Alvarez fled the vehicle before the crash, which resulted in multiple deaths and injuries.
Initially intending to end his life, Alvarez changed his mind at the last moment.
Authorities found him bleeding near the scene.
Alvarez's motive stemmed from personal issues, including a troubled marriage.
Despite facing homicide charges, Alvarez expressed remorse for the preventable disaster he caused.
The incident left a trail of destruction and loss, highlighting the devastating consequences of mental health crises.
